<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06288040 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06288040 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  BankAmerica Corp. has agreed to buy a Hawaiian savings and loan from a SanFrancisco-based investor group headed by former Treasury Secretary WilliamSimon and former Federal Reserve Board Vice Chairman Preston Martin. HonfedBank, Hawaii's third-largest financial institution, is the ninth purchase byBankAmerica this year. Honfed is one of the nation's strongest thrifts with $3billion in assets and 29 branches on four Hawaiian islands. Officials wouldn'tdisclose terms of the acquisition.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BOFA TO BUY HAWAIIAN Sandamp;L  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Financial Digest  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff and Wire Reports  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911014  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  78  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, October 14, 199100288040,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>